		<hra:heidicon>
			<hra:item type="f_description" status="0"  display="Kommentar">
				<hra:value>explanatory comments/crosstagging:
Usually puja would be directed towards a physical icon of some sort, and in the example on the right, we see another young woman holding a burning lamp before a light-colored statue of Krishna Gopala playing his flute. The scene is indoors, in a domestic shrine-room, and we can see a fuller display of the paraphernalia of worship: the standing oil-lamp, the platter with jasmine flowers and bananas, the water vessel, and the bells hanging above. (Richard H. Davis)(gs)</hra:value>
				<hra:value>related literature:
Davis, Richard H. 2010. &quot;Temple in a Frame. God Posters For and Of Worship&quot; http://www.tasveergharindia.net/cmsdesk/essay/97/index.html (10.01.2011)(gs)</hra:value>
			</hra:item>
